status: MARC21-007: Color characteristics of the nonprojected graphic
Color characteristics of the nonprojected graphic.

definition (en): Printed or executed in a single color.
scope note (en): Used for monochrome art works. It is not used with photographic materials. Does not include black.
Refers to monochrome photographic materials executed in black-and-white.

definition (en): Printed or executed in more than one color.
Image, produced by a printing or photographic process, is hand colored.
scope note (en): Rarely used with commercial visual materials since these are not typically issued with hand coloring.

definition (en): Work or collection is a combination of one color, black-and-white, multicolored, hand colored, and/or other images.
Color characteristics of the item are not known.
Color other than one color, black-and-white, multicolored, hand colored, mixed.
scope note (en): Includes stained, tinted, or toned items(e.g., sepia toned photographic items).
